FBIS4-39214 "drsov109_t_94001" FBIS-SOV-94-109 Daily Report 7 Jun 1994 BALTIC STATES Estonia Russian Deputy Foreign Minister Arrives in Tallinn Russian Deputy Foreign Minister Arrives in Tallinn LD0706094994 Tallinn Radio Tallinn Network in Estonian 0900 GMT 7 Jun 94 LD0706094994 Tallinn Radio Tallinn Network Estonian BFN [Text] Russian Deputy Foreign Minister Vitaliy Churkin has arrived in Estonia. More details now from Hillar Nahkmann who has just returned from Tallinn airport. [Nahkmann] Vitaliy Churkin was welcomed by Raul Malk, his interlocutor at the negotiations table. Both men emphasized that this is already their second meeting, continuing the talks which began in Geneva. During the meeting in Geneva there was a very friendly and warm atmosphere. Today and tomorrow the two major issues of the Estonia-Russian talks will be under discussion -- troop withdrawal and the future of the pensioners, Russian military pensioners, and their status in Estonia. Both men were reluctant to speak about this issue. [passage indistinct]
